                h3 About the project
                p
                    | Tran3D is 
                    span.highlight an online 3D printing service platform
                    |  where distributed 3D printing resources are gathered, shared, and applied.
        
                h3 How it works
                p 
                    | Tran3D runs a C2C business model. It facilitates transactions between 
                    span.highlight 3D printer owners and people who want to make 3D prints
                    | . Service bureaus can join the platform to offer 3D printing services while customers can select one of the best solutions we recommend to get their customized 3D models printed.
                h3 My roles
                p 
                    | Being one of the co-founders, I led the 
                    span.highlight UI/UX design and front-end development
                    |  from start to finish last year. 
                p As a designer in particular, I worked on
                .flex.wider
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span User research
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Sketches and wireframes
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Visual and interaction design
                p Then I turned the design into product with code. 
                h3 How I started
                p Working closely with my partners, I first made a Q&A sheet that depicts our potential users.
                .board
                    h3 User Brief
                    h4 Who are the target audiences?
                    p Modern people who enjoy customizing things or transforming ideas into reality using technology.
                    h4 What are the audience types and their differences?
                    p 
                        | There are basically three types. 1. 
                        b Common individuals
                        | —people who need 3D printed products, but without 3D printers; 2. 
                        b Designers
                        | —people who are capable of producing high-quality 3D models consistently; 3. 
                        b Manufacturers
                        | —people who own 3D printers, can either be individuals or companies.
                    h4 Where can audiences be found?
                    p Most likely, they can be found in universities or in manufactural industry. They might also have active accounts in 3D forums.
                    h4 What personality does Tran3D want to project to the audience?
                    p Simple, rapid, technological, playful and high quality.
                p Based on the user brief, I interviewed 50 people via questionnaires and finally planned out our 
                    span.highlight design goals
                    | .
                .flex.wider
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span To facilitate an intuitive and seamless experience when it comes to customizing 3D printing products
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span To design a personable and engaging user interface
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span To create convenient and powerful functionalities that manage services and transactions
                p 
