                h2 START A 3D PRINT
                .sep.taller
                h3 The Problem
                p 3D printing features rapid prototyping and product customization. It enables consumer products to be made on­-demand, eliminating the restriction to craftsmanship and manufacture, as well as reducing the waste from overproduction and overpricing.
                p
                    | So here comes the problem—
                    span.highlight how can I get customers onboard and fully deliver such quality of 3D printing to them?
                h3 The Analysis
                p
                    | To introduce complex technology home, Tran3D must provide customers with an easy and fast channel to getting their hands on real 3D printed products. 
                    span.highlight The main idea was to build a module that helps users start a 3D print and guides them quickly through a customization workflow before they reach the shopping cart.
                    |  I called it "Start a 3D Print". Some core principles were identified:
                .flex
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Prominent elements—CTAs draw attentions and trigger interests. 
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Easy start—Tasks that are easier to do are a better starting point for people with low motivation (see BJ Fogg Behavior Model).
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Limited choices—It’s often easier to make a decision when presented with only a few options.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Hidden expert-level interfaces and terminologies—Expert users are the minority.
                    .illustration
                        img(src="assets/img/bj-model.png")
                p
                    | Overall, I wanted to make this module accessible and easy to users and boost their engagement. The customization workflow of 3D print should be 
                    span.highlight lucid
                    | , 
                    span.highlight fast
                    | , 
                    span.highlight efficient
                    | , and 
                    span.highlight interesting
                    | .
                h3 The Exploring
                p 
                    | Based on the analysis, I started my exploration by scoping the workflow into three phases: 
                    span.highlight Upload Your Models
                    | , 
                    span.highlight Select a Material
                    | , and 
                    span.highlight Choose a 3D Printing Service
                    | . In this way, a complex and tedious process was effectively decomposed into parts whose tasks are easier to understand and goals are clearer to achieve.
        .level.level--swans-down
            .container
                img(src="assets/img/customize-process.svg")
        .level
            .container
                p I then started to play with a few key design concepts by creating mid-fidelity wireframes. Those concepts were:
                .flex.wider
                    ul
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Create visually striking call-to-actions that compel users to click.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Start from the task that is easiest and most requisite.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Unlock the next phase until the current one is completed, bringing fewer choices for users.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Prioritize imperative parameters, use straightforward wording and hide expert-level content. Complex interfaces and terminologies are not only overwhelming for beginners, but could also be difficult to use for experts in certain cases.
                        li
                            i.icon.icon-li.ion-chevron-right
                            span Integrate all three phases in one page for an unbreakable experience. This integrity keeps data consistent and interaction coherent.
